title: Useeum

creator: Useeum
descriptionHtml:
Useeum provides a variety of engaging stories, games and other exciting experiences at museums, science centres, nature parks and similar places.

Whether you are a tourist or avid visitor of museums Useeum offers unique museum experiences. Our app offers many different guides and games that will make your museum visit a great experience for both young and old.

With the Useeum app you can find outdoor as well as indoor audio guides and games which are both fun and educational for the whole family.

MUSEUMS AND EXPERIENCES IN THE APP
Whether you are interested in art, history, science or nature you can find narratives, audio guides or games that are perfect for you. In the Useeum app you will find art museums, historical museum and natural history museums, science centres as well as outdoor experiences in forests and parks. It will be exciting to explore our different games and guides!

SOME OF THE PLACES YOU CAN VISIT WITH THE APP
The Labour Museum in Oslo
Billund Kommunes Museer
The Bornholm Art Museum
The Museum of Oslo
Christiansborg Palace
Danmarks Borgcenter
Danish Jewish Museum
Egeskov
Fiskeri og Søfartsmuseet
Flyvestation Værløse
Frederiksberg Stadsarkiv
Frøslevlejrens Museum
H. C. Andersen’s house
Hammershus
Historiens Hus
The Karen Blixen Museum
Kierkegaard by Nature
Stevnsfort Cold War Museum
Magasin du Nord Museet
Museet for Religiøs Kunst
The Narvik War Museum
Parkmuseerne
Roskilde Museum
Royal College of Nursing
Tidens Samling
Slesvigske Vognsamling
Steno Museet
Sønderborg Castle
Greenhouses and Botanical Garden in Aarhus
Nørre Vosborg

EDUCATIONAL GAMES
In the Useeum app you will find games for kids of all ages. The games are designed to be both educational and entertaining. The games can be played with the family during a museum visit but are also ideal for schools or as a supplement for curriculums.

These are of some the games you can find in the Useeum app: Nature Quest, The Astral Journey, The Mystery at Hammershus, The Museum Mystery, Mytedetektiverne, Mysteriet om Dannebrog, The Mystery of Hammershus, Parforcejagt and OppermannMysteriet.

In the Museum Mystery you will be helping professor Blom stop Heidenreich from stealing a unique item. The Museum Mystery can be played at Christiansborg Palace in Copenhagen, at Roskilde Museum, in the city of Roskilde, at Egeskov on Funen, at Nørre Vosborg and at Hammershus on Bornholm.

The Museum Mystery has been created in cooperation with OK Monkey.
OK Monkey are experts at engaging children. They formerly worked at DR Ramasjang where they created entertaining TV for children and entire universes for kids like the Ramasjang app and Ramasjang Mysteriet. They also write children books and have written the script for Cirkus Summarum.

ENGAGING STORIES
In the app you can experience entertaining and educational stories. Our audio guides are stories that will take you on a journey to the past or portray great personalities like Karen Blixen, H C Andersen and Søren Kierkegaard. Exiting narratives such as Kings in the Tapestries at Christiansborg Palace, The Rise and Fall of Roskilde in Roskilde, The seventies at the Museum of Oslo in Oslo, Danmarks Vildeste Fiskereventyr at Fiskeri- og Søfartsmuseet in Esbjerg, Danmarks sidste vikingekonge at Historiens Hus in Odense, Danskernes dagligdag i det 20. århundrede at Tidens Samling in Odense, Rundt om Magasin - Købmænd, mode og æggesalat at Magasin Museet in Copenhagen.

In The Greenhouses and and Botanical Garden's plant guide you will find comprehensive information about their plants.

LOCATIONS
Whether you are in Denmark, England or Norway great experiences are waiting for you. So if you are planning a museum visit in Copenhagen, Aarhus, Odense, Roskilde, Esbjerg, Billund, Narvik, Oslo, London, Nordsjælland, Sønderjylland, Syddanmark, Bornholm, Fyn, Jylland, Midtjylland or one of the other places featuring great guides and experiences – download our app for free – Useeum.

Check out our guides and games – have fun!
